LOGIC 1: REVERSED STRING (With storing the reversed string in a variable)


public class Main
{
	public static void main(String[] args) {
	    String a="ABIRAMI";
	    String a2="";
	    for(int i=a.length()-1;i>=0;i--)//i<7-1;i>=0;print();6 decremented to 5
	    {
	        a2=a2+a.charAt(i);//""+I="I"
	    }
		System.out.println("The reversed string is :"+a2);
	}
}

output:
The reversed string is : IMARIBA

LOGIC 2: REVERSED STRING (Without storing the reversed string in a variable)

public class Main
{
	public static void main(String[] args) {
	    String a="ABIRAMI";
	    
	    for(int i=a.length()-1;i>=0;i--)//i<7-1;i>=0;print();6 decremented to 5
	    {
	       
		System.out.print(a.charAt(i));
	    }
	}
}

output:
      IMARIBA
